@nick_skeyes invites us to enjoy tulip season in Netherlands 😍🌷
The tulip season in the Netherlands typically begins in late March and lasts until mid-May, with peak bloom usually occurring in mid-April.
Mesmerizing hues of millions of tulips create a breathtaking panorama, drawing people from every corner of the globe to witness nature’s kaleidoscope.

Meet the leaf sheep, a tiny sea slug that looks like a cartoon sheep 🐑 This amazing creature is one of the select few in the world that can use algae for photosynthesis. It gets its energy from the sun, just like plants. Astonishing, right? 🌱⁣

Dog sledding in Finland by @travelingwithsue 🐕🛷❄️🇫🇮
.
Dog sledding in Finland offers a thrilling experience, combining the beauty of the Arctic landscape with the agility of these remarkable sled dogs. The crisp air, snowy trails, and the bond formed with the huskies create a memorable adventure. Tag who you’d like to ride with! 😍❄️🙌🏼
.
Note: these dogs are very well taken care of by the owners. They are happy and excited to do the sled. They bark excitedly and wagging their tails before and after the ride 😃😃🐕🐕
